<title>Jessica Shortall: The US needs paid family leave -- for the sake of its future | TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript | TED.com</title>
<meta content="Jessica Shortall: The US needs paid family leave -- for the sake of its future | TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript | TED.com" name="title" />
<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: We need women to work, and we need working women to have babies. So why is America one of the only countries in the world that offers no national paid leave to new working mothers? In this incisive talk, Jessica Shortall makes the impassioned case that the reality of new working motherhood in America is both hidden and horrible: millions of women, every year, are forced back to work within just weeks of giving birth. Her idea worth spreading: the time has come for us to recognize the economic, physical and psychological costs of our approach to working mothers and their babies, and to secure our economic future by providing paid leave to all working parents." name="description" />
